This week has been a rollercoaster of emotions. 😢 As much as I’m excited for the new baby, I also feel the sadness and loss of seeing Jayla mature into her big sister role. It breaks my heart seeing Jayla express her feelings like this.💔Trying my best to hold it together and show her how much she’s still loved and how our love for her will never change even with a new addition in our family. We made this house our home for 4 wonderful years. In each room, in front of every wall, and in between all the little corners - you’ll find pieces of my heart. Little pieces made up of memories when Kennedy and Jayla still needed me to hold them and when they still needed me to help them pour cereal into a bowl. This house holds so many memories of firsts. First day of school, first time baking, first birthday party..

(Crying while I’m writing this 😭)

Now, we are starting a new chapter in Florida. In a new home that will be filled with so many more new memories. 🥹 tbh I feel scared, uncomfortable, and a bit sad to leave everything we know and everyone we love in Chicago. But I know everything will be okay in the end because I have the four most important people in my life right next to me. They’re the pieces to all those little memories that fill my heart. ❤️ we can’t wait to take you guys on this new adventure with us. 🥰 (also, living close to Disney World is going to be a new experience 😬)

“Why does Disney mean so much to you?”

Coming from first generation immigrant parents, my family never had the time or the money to take me to Disney. Now with 3 kids of my own and having memories of each one of them at Disney makes me feel so fortunate and grateful. I know they’re young and Leia probably won’t remember much right now but I’ll always remember that I got to share these experiences with them. And maybe one day they’ll look back on these photos and recreate them with their own kids ❤️

In just 4 days, Kennedy turns 10 years old. When I look at these films, I think of a time in my life when I was struggling to be a mom. It’s amazing to think that she’s been my best friend and has gone through so many different phases of life with me. It’s been the two of us since day 1 and now I can confidently say that I’ve finally given her the mom and the life she has always deserved. ❤️

Today, instead of missing the little versions of you that’s gone, I took a minute and looked closer at the person you are now. You are so much of what this world needs. You’re compassionate, understanding, and you care so deeply for every person who walks into your life. I love how our conversations have evolved and all the random facts you like to tell. Lol I love how you dance to every song that comes on and the way you express your emotions so confidently. I’m so thankful I get to see you in this world and watch you grow into this incredible little person every year. Happy 10th Birthday Kennedy! You’re in your double digits era ☺️🎂🎉🥳
